List all PieHelper options:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a "PieHelper" | more
List all read/write PieHelper options:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a "PieHelper" -t rw | more
List all read-only PieHelper options:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a "PieHelper" -t ro | more
Show PieHelper option values (With variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a "PieHelper" -g
Show PieHelper option values (With variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a "PieHelper" -g -r
Change the value of selected PieHelper options (With variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a "PieHelper" -s
Change the value of selected PieHelper options (With variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a "PieHelper" -s -r
Change the value of all PieHelper options:ph_configure_app_options "PieHelper"
Reset all PieHelper options to default values (Debug will not be affected):for PH_k in PH_PIEH_PERSISTENT PH_PIEH_CMD_OPTS PH_PIEH_CIFS_SHARE PH_PIEH_CIFS_USER PH_PIEH_CIFS_PASS PH_PIEH_CIFS_SRV PH_PIEH_CIFS_DIR PH_PIEH_CIFS_SUBDIR PH_PIEH_CIFS_MPT PH_PIEH_PRE_CMD PH_PIEH_POST_CMD PH_PIEH_PKG_NAME PH_PIEH_SANITY;do;ph_set_option_to_default_value "$PH_k";PH_OPTIONS="";unset PH_k;done
Display help about selected PieHelper options (With variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a "PieHelper" -d
Display help about selected PieHelper options (With variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a "PieHelper" -d -r
Go to menu "PieHelper":ph_show_menu "PieHelper"
Go to menu "Main":ph_show_menu Main
Go to menu "Apps":ph_show_menu Apps
Open Shell to home directory (Type "CTRL-D" to return):cd;/bin/bash
Return to previous screen:return
